Materials and methods
pQTL dataset
Cis-protein quantitative trait loci (cis-pQTLs) are found in close proximity to their respective target genes or proteins. This study referenced two sources of pQTL data, which included 738 cis-SNPs associated with 734 proteins from the work of Zheng et al. [
38
], as well as supplementary pQTL data from the deCODE database [
39
]. Instrumental variables for cis-pQTLs were selected according to specific criteria: a p-value threshold of less than 5 × 10^−8, exclusion of SNPs located within the major histocompatibility complex (MHC) region [
40
], inclusion of SNPs situated within 1 MB of the gene, and a linkage disequilibrium threshold of r²
41
]. All datasets employed in this analysis were derived from individuals of European ancestry.

